tion-transform duration-200 shrink-0 -rotate-90"><div style="width: 12px; height: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M14.128 7.165a.502.502 0 0 1 .744.67l-4.5 5-.078.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.666-.07l-4.5-5-.06-.082a.501.501 0 0 1 .729-.656l.075.068L10 11.752z"></path></svg></div></span></div></button></div><span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite">Viewed a file, created a file, read a file</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Here's your fixed code. All 3 problems are solved:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>What's fixed:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>1 — Page no longer shifts</strong> — The old code touched <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">document.body</code> overflow which caused the scroll jump. This version uses <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">position: fixed</code> with <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">pointer-events: none</code> until it's ready. Your store layout is completely untouched.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>2 — Running stick figures are now clearly visible</strong> — Each runner has a red square with a white <strong>N</strong> on their head (the Netflix logo), a white stick body, swinging arms, and running legs with proper animation. Both enter from opposite sides.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>3 — Redirects to your Deals &amp; Offers page</strong> — At the very top of the code find this line and update the URL to match your actual page:</p>
<div role="group" aria-label="Code" tabindex="0" class="relative group/copy bg-bg-000/50 border-0.5 border-border-400 rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-accent-100"><div class="sticky opacity-0 group-hover/copy:opacity-100 group-focus-within/copy:opacity-100 top-2 py-2 h-12 w-0 float-right"><div class="absolute right-0 h-8 px-2 items-center inline-flex z-10"><button class="inline-flex
