d-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">That fingerprint square above is your favicon. <strong>Right click it → Save image as → name it <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">favicon.png</code> → save to Desktop.</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Then:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">GitHub → Sky-Blueprint → <strong>Add file → Upload files</strong> → upload <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">favicon.png</code> → Commit</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">GitHub → click <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> → click the <strong>pencil ✏️</strong> icon to edit → find the line that says <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">&lt;title&gt;Sky Blueprint</code> → paste this <strong>above</strong> it:</li>
</ol>
